chunk_content: Naming Convention for MER Result and Target Review Favorites in DATIM MER Indicator Name Numerator or Denominator O V E R V I PEPFAR FY24Q1 Results <Indicator> <‘N’ or ‘D’> <Disaggregation, if any> E W Completeness Review Pivot Fiscal Year and Reporting Period Disaggregation Name (e.g., quarter) (e.g., Age/Sex/KnownNewResult) If an indicator is calculated by auto-summing other indicators and/or disaggregates, AUTO-SUM” will be present in the favorite’s name (as seen underlined in the example for HTS_SELF found below). Also, for testing indicators, “Facility” or “Community” will appear after the fiscal year and reporting section of the favorite name to easily discern testing modalities.
